- Order ids (s<N>/d<N>) are now generated by the server, seeded on startup
  from the highest id already in the DB (OrderDao.getMaxIdSuffix), so
  numbering stays unique across restarts
- SupplyOrderRequest/DemandOrderRequest no longer accept an orderId field
- OrderResponse still returns the (now auto-generated) orderId
- New GET /api/orders/{orderId}/status: returns PENDING / PARTIALLY_FILLED /
  FILLED plus the trades the order has been part of; checks the live
  in-memory ledger first, falls back to the DB (covers orders from before
  a restart); unknown id -> 404 via new OrderNotFoundException
- Postman collection updated: capture-id test scripts, status-lookup
  requests, renumbered validation/error examples
